{
  "stem": "24111.7",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Avien, ?] my mother, and they which were left, they join hands, walked across, and pulled, by joined hands, the whole group over.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And not one of the children was lost.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "By the way, I would-- I forgot to mention something.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Joschko took along four British officers which were hiding in the area when they escaped out of the British camp.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we thought having British with us, it would help us perhaps in negotiation with the Swiss.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They disappeared.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And Joschko took also an Tunisian family, a Jewish family, with very old people along.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they made him a terrible hard time because they shouted and-- in situations where the children were quiet and were deadly afraid that the Germans or the Swiss will catch them.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They were not even cooperating with that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But Joschko took them along.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And when they crossed the border-- when they crossed the river and they were on the other side, they found Swiss soldiers.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And in the first moment, Joschko thought that they're Germans because their uniform is green, and in the night you cannot really differentiate.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But they were actually Swiss soldiers.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they took them, as wet and as dripping with water, and they brought them to a-- to a building.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But they didn't allow them and didn't give them the assurance of entry.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "By crossing the river, all belongings the children carried were lost.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They were taken away with the water.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The beautiful part is that on the other side, Swiss people were able to-- to save the belongings.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They-- it washed up on the-- on the river.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And most of the things came back to the group and to Joschko.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And a few of the documents I showed you survived that way.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
